  <h2 class="decisions-text problem" style="margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Proxima Nova Bold;">design <br> decisions üë©‚Äçüíª</h2>
<section class="decisions">
  <%= image_tag("covid-1.svg", class: "covid1") %>
  <div class="finding" style="align-self: center">
    <%= image_tag("marker-1.svg") %>
    <p>Researchers expressed the need for a clean UI that condenses dense amounts of information into a quickly scannable interface. I chose to include a toggle for less and more information to allow for scrolling of the page without the need to click through to understand the research more deeply. Aesthetics were largely sacrificed for usability and readability.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="finding2 finding" style="align-self: center">
    <%= image_tag("marker-2.svg") %>
    <p>We needed to create an admin interface to accept and reject research summaries. I designed this interface with the intention of reusing components from the public interface to save development time. I included large indicators of red and green to quickly show to the admin the state of each research paper. </p>
  </div>
  <%= image_tag("covid-2.svg", class: "covid2") %>
  <%= image_tag("covid-3.svg", class: "covid3") %>
  <div class="finding3 finding" style="align-self: center">
    <%= image_tag("marker-3.svg") %>
    <p>I took design references from Google, Wikipedia and ResearchGate to develop an interface that would be familiar and trusted by researchers. The colors, font, font size ratios, spacing and overall feel of the UI was influenced from these sources that researchers already use on a day to day basis.</p>
  </div>
</section>
